# Vormia Inertia ‚Äî Vue 3 guide

## Overview

Use this guide when the stack is **Laravel + vormiaphp/vormia + vormiaphp/vormia-inertia + Inertia Vue 3**. Laravel renders Inertia responses; **Vue Single File Components** (`.vue`) are the page layer. Prefer **Composition API** with **`<script setup>`** for new code.

## Tech stack (align versions with your lockfiles)

- **Laravel** 12+.
- **inertiajs/inertia-laravel** ‚Äî server side.
- **@inertiajs/vue3** ‚Äî `createInertiaApp`, `usePage`, `router`, `Link`, `Head`, `useForm`.
- **@inertiajs/vite** ‚Äî Vite plugin.
- **@vitejs/plugin-vue** ‚Äî compiles `.vue` in Vite.
- **Vue 3** ‚Äî [vuejs.org](https://vuejs.org/guide/introduction.html).

Official Inertia entry points for Vue:

- [Client-side setup ‚Äî Vue](https://inertiajs.com/client-side-setup#vue)
- [Pages](https://inertiajs.com/pages), [Links](https://inertiajs.com/links), [Forms](https://inertiajs.com/forms), [Shared data](https://inertiajs.com/shared-data)

## File structure (convention)

```
resources/js/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app.ts                  # createInertiaApp + createApp
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Pages/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Layouts/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ AppLayout.vue
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Components/
```

Keep the **page name** string in `Inertia::render()` aligned with the resolver (often `Pages/Foo/Bar` ‚Üí `./Pages/Foo/Bar.vue`).

## Page component (`<script setup>`)

Props are passed from Laravel as component props. You can type them with TypeScript or runtime `defineProps`.

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
defineProps<{ user: { name: string } }>()
</script>

<template>
  <div>Hello, {{ user.name }}</div>
</template>
```

## Shared props and Vormia

In **`HandleInertiaRequests::share()`**, expose things like:

- **`notification`** ‚Äî flash/session notification for a global toast or modal.
- **`auth`** ‚Äî minimal user for the layout.
- **`vormia`** ‚Äî public configuration hints only.

In Vue, use **`usePage()`** from `@inertiajs/vue3`:

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { usePage } from '@inertiajs/vue3'

const page = usePage<{ notification?: unknown }>()
// page.props.notification
</script>
```

## Navigation

- **`<Link :href="url">`** ‚Äî preferred for declarative navigation.
- **`router.visit(url)`** ‚Äî imperative; supports [visit options](https://inertiajs.com/manual-visits).

With **Wayfinder**, import typed route helpers instead of stringly-typed paths where possible.

## Forms

Use **`useForm`** from `@inertiajs/vue3` for Inertia form state and Laravel validation errors. See [Inertia forms ‚Äî Vue](https://inertiajs.com/forms#vue).

## MediaForge rule of thumb

Resolve **`MediaForge::url()`** (public or signed) in PHP and pass URLs into `Inertia::render()`. Vue should bind `src`/`href` to those strings rather than reconstructing S3 or storage URLs from secrets in the browser.

## Persistent layouts

Use Inertia‚Äôs [persistent layouts](https://inertiajs.com/pages#persistent-layouts) pattern so shell UI (nav, toasts) does not remount on every navigation.

## Checklist (new screen)

1. Route + controller + policy (Laravel).
2. `Inertia::render('Pages/...', $props)`.
3. Matching `.vue` page under the resolver path.
4. Links with `<Link>` or `router.visit`.
5. Media: server-side Vormia processing; props carry displayable URLs.

